name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: Our evening seminar for Idaho parents and educators is now 8 days away. Presenters include ICAC investigators as well as a prosecutor in the U.S. Attorney's Office. Details on the April 6 virtual event are available here:

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: My office has entered into an agreement with federal investigators to join forces in targeting the global plague of robocalls. News release:   https://t.co/ghvlXnHYGp

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: Thank you for helping get the word out about this emerging consumer protection issue here in Idaho.

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: On April 6 at 7 PM MDT, Idaho's Internet Crimes Against Children Unit will host a statewide seminar for parents and educators. "Digital Dangers: Helping Idaho Adults Protect Children Online" will be streamed via YouTube. Details:  https://t.co/KRSWEZNhaF  https://t.co/apa65g30rA

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: Presenters will include ICAC experts, an Idaho pediatrician who will discuss the mental health effects of unhealthy digital habits, as well as a federal attorney who prosecutes sexual predators.

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: On April 6 at 7:00 PM MDT, investigators with the Idaho Internet Crimes Against Children Unit will hold a statewide seminar to help parents and educators better understand the dangers young people face online. More:   https://t.co/Qm5R1WI3L5  https://t.co/BiDHbEOiI6

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: A new development in Idaho's participation in the national opioid settlements means the state will obtain its maximum $119M allotment and do so on an accelerated timeline. Full news release:  https://t.co/0lVoHhgTHQ

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: Protesting is a Constitutionally-guaranteed right. But targeting and attempting to intimidate social workers, police officers and members of the judiciary who are simply doing their jobs to protect a vulnerable human life goes too far. My recent statement:  https://t.co/ArXzVsfvwH

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: I've issued a statement on Idaho's child protection system and the recent actions of some protestors.  https://t.co/ArXzVsfvwH

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: Motor vehicle-related complaints have been my office’s top complaint category for the last six years. These complaints may be related to new or used cars as well as vehicle repairs. When buying a vehicle, do your research. #NCPW2022 #ConsumerProtection  https://t.co/craR6rXCe8

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: Home improvement projects, especially when a contractor is required, can be complicated and costly. Check out my office’s Idaho Consumer Protection Manual at  https://t.co/YCLy6UooOO for tips on choosing a contractor. #NCPW2022 #ConsumerProtection  https://t.co/tSLOgZc25U

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: In 2021, my office’s Consumer Protection Division received 1,165 consumer complaints. The top 3 complaint categories were motor vehicles, construction, and landlord/tenant matters. If you have a problem with a business, file a complaint at  https://t.co/YCLy6U6Nqe. #NCPW2022  https://t.co/TQ2YNS2vPl

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: One more event to mention at 5PM MT: Join a Facebook Live w/ the FTC and the Social Security Administration’s (SSA’s) Office of the Inspector General. You’ll learn how to spot and avoid government impersonator scams. Please join and bring your questions!  https://t.co/Ch5MDG6xae

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: 1PM MT: Join the Twitter chat in English with @FTC, @USAGov, @SocialSecurity. Follow the conversation by using hashtags #SlamTheScamChat and #NCPW2022.

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: Join  NCPW Twitter chats on avoiding Coronavirus and imposter scams. 11AM MT: Join the Twitter chat in Spanish with @laFTC, @USAGovEspanol and @SeguroSocial. Follow the conversation by using hashtags #OjoConLasEstafas and #NCPW2022  https://t.co/azo7F3EKGM

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: If you receive a suspicious call, text, or email that mentions Social Security, ignore it and report it to  https://t.co/MXdSFSWUD4. Report other government impostor scams to  https://t.co/AoehT9aLyZ #SlamTheScam #NCPW2022 #ConsumerProtection  https://t.co/TznMgFz0LC

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: Today is packed with opportunities to participate in National Consumer Protection Week Twitter chats, webinars, and Facebook Live events. Join one and learn how to protect yourself from scams. #NCPW2022 #ConsumerProtection  #SlamTheScam  https://t.co/2P4vrN1QcP

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: Most cell phones have call blocking services to block scam calls before your phone rings. This shows 3 of 41 blocked calls an Idahoan received from the same number in less than a minute. Talk to your cell provider about installing a call blocker if you don’t have one. #NCPW2022  https://t.co/MLwjnZ9WS4

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: You can take steps to cut down on unwanted calls, including robocalls. My office advises that you let unknown calls go to voicemail. Follow these tips to protect yourself and help minimize the number of unwanted calls you receive. #NCPW2022 #ConsumerProtection  https://t.co/FJYWh54o5M

name: Lawrence G. Wasden
tweet: Unwanted  calls are a nationwide problem and Idaho is not immune to them. Technology makes it cheap and easy for scammers to make these calls. #NCPW2022 #ConsumerProtection  https://t.co/U740UhhdQZ
